1
00:00:11,778 --> 00:00:14,313
"I'm sorry. I did it."

2
00:00:14,314 --> 00:00:17,349
INTERNATIONAL INVESTIGATION DIVISION
HIGASHI SHINJUKU POLICE STATION

3
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:18,752
That's good.

4
00:00:19,652 --> 00:00:21,053
Listen.

5
00:00:21,054 --> 00:00:23,255
You might think no one's watching,

6
00:00:23,256 --> 00:00:26,659
but God always sees everything.
Do you understand?

7
00:00:28,595 --> 00:00:32,399
MOMIJI IMAI
(VIETNAMESE INTERPRETER)

8
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:38,038
"Heaven's vengeance is slow but sure!"

9
00:00:39,172 --> 00:00:41,641
So, don't ever do
something like this again.

10
00:00:46,112 --> 00:00:49,148
"Heaven's" um...

11
00:00:49,149 --> 00:00:51,317
Hold on a moment. "...is slow but..."

12
00:00:52,018 --> 00:00:56,588
Detective Iiyama from Higashi Shinjuku
can be very calm and compassionate.

13
00:00:56,589 --> 00:00:58,991
He's definitely a great detective.

14
00:00:58,992 --> 00:01:02,528
<i>But he doesn't really think
that his words need to be translated</i>

15
00:01:02,529 --> 00:01:04,431
<i>into another language.</i>

16
00:01:04,998 --> 00:01:07,666
There are quite a few detectives
who tend to rely

17
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:09,568
too much on sayings and proverbs.

18
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:12,939
- It sounds great to Japanese ears.
- Right.

19
00:01:13,506 --> 00:01:15,374
Every language and culture
has its own nuances,

20
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:18,577
so it doesn't always resonate
with everyone.

21
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:20,646
And each country
has its own unique sayings.

22
00:01:20,647 --> 00:01:21,847
For example, this...

23
00:01:21,848 --> 00:01:23,550
Mr. Arikino, what do you think

24
00:01:24,117 --> 00:01:25,819
about detectives who often quote proverbs?

25
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:28,354
Um...

26
00:01:29,355 --> 00:01:31,224
I suppose it's fine.

27
00:01:31,858 --> 00:01:35,395
Our job is to interpret exactly
what the speakers say,

28
00:01:36,329 --> 00:01:38,832
not necessarily what resonates
with the listener.

29
00:01:40,433 --> 00:01:43,202
Arikino, can I speak to you for a moment?

30
00:01:43,203 --> 00:01:44,237
Sure, sir.

31
00:01:49,876 --> 00:01:52,811
Don't involve Mr. Arikino so suddenly.

32
00:01:52,812 --> 00:01:55,582
I just wanted to know what he thought.

33
00:01:56,716 --> 00:01:58,217
Speaking of Higashi Shinjuku,

34
00:01:58,218 --> 00:02:01,453
the lady detective I interpreted for
the other day was so nice to work with.

35
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:03,188
She doesn't omit subjects or predicates,

36
00:02:03,189 --> 00:02:06,024
and she avoids
ambiguous Japanese expressions.

37
00:02:06,025 --> 00:02:09,162
She also had an unusual hair color
for a detective.

38
00:02:11,064 --> 00:02:16,069
Recently, there have been more cases
of electric bike batteries being stolen.

39
00:02:17,036 --> 00:02:21,574
YURI KIYOMIYA
(SINHALA INTERPRETER)

40
00:02:23,109 --> 00:02:26,479
Actually, Ashan,
I think your idea was brilliant.

41
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:29,515
- Excuse me?
- If you stole the entire bike,

42
00:02:29,516 --> 00:02:32,151
it would be easily traced
by its registration number.

43
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:34,486
But if you steal just the battery,

44
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:37,290
even if it's found,
you can't prove it was stolen.

45
00:02:38,124 --> 00:02:40,292
It's not something you should be praising.

46
00:02:40,293 --> 00:02:41,728
Oops, I'm sorry.

47
00:02:42,662 --> 00:02:44,096
But I want to know.

48
00:02:44,097 --> 00:02:48,300
You had three batteries in your backpack.

49
00:02:48,301 --> 00:02:50,103
What were you planning to do with them?

50
00:02:50,904 --> 00:02:52,705
Were you selling them to someone?

51
00:03:11,991 --> 00:03:12,892
By the way, Ashan...

52
00:03:14,227 --> 00:03:16,596
You work at a Sri Lankan restaurant, right?

53
00:03:20,066 --> 00:03:21,367
Which dish would you recommend?

54
00:03:25,805 --> 00:03:26,906
Excuse me?

55
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:36,182
"Kehel Kore Bath"?

56
00:03:37,283 --> 00:03:39,952
Rice wrapped in a banana leaf?

57
00:03:39,953 --> 00:03:41,554
That sounds really nice.

58
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:03,141
Isn't that Arikino,
who was stationed here before?

59
00:04:03,142 --> 00:04:05,278
He has quite the audacity to show up here.

60
00:04:07,447 --> 00:04:12,085
INTERNATIONAL INVESTIGATION DIVISION
KAMIAZABU POLICE STATION

61
00:04:19,692 --> 00:04:22,060
I'm Arikino, a Chinese interpreter.

62
00:04:22,061 --> 00:04:24,297
I was assigned here
for a voluntary interview.

63
00:04:25,598 --> 00:04:28,768
I didn't expect this,
though I told them anyone would do.

64
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:33,339
Oh, well. Just go through this beforehand.

65
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:38,244
A condominium resident in Minato Ward
called early this morning,

66
00:04:39,012 --> 00:04:42,914
reporting that the Chinese couple
next door was fighting.

67
00:04:42,915 --> 00:04:44,716
What's the matter?

68
00:04:44,717 --> 00:04:46,152
Are you all right?

69
00:04:49,489 --> 00:04:53,091
- Stop!
- You worthless scumbag!

70
00:04:53,092 --> 00:04:56,728
Calm down, you stupid woman!

71
00:04:56,729 --> 00:05:01,701
I never want to see your face again.

72
00:05:02,268 --> 00:05:05,804
We asked them to come here voluntarily
after the husband claimed

73
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:07,340
he was assaulted by his wife.

74
00:05:10,209 --> 00:05:11,811
How long have you been married?

75
00:05:17,617 --> 00:05:18,685
"For three years."

76
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:21,520
Our records show multiple reports

77
00:05:21,521 --> 00:05:24,324
of you fighting with your husband
in the past.

78
00:05:38,471 --> 00:05:41,840
She looks like a typical woman
from the continent.

79
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:45,311
It must be tough for the husband
to live with someone like her.

80
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:47,780
Don't translate it.

81
00:05:49,649 --> 00:05:52,318
Tell me, how did you hit him?

82
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:55,321
Come on, translate.

83
00:05:56,155 --> 00:05:59,124
Are you asking what the trigger was
for hitting him?

84
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:00,926
What else could it possibly mean?

85
00:06:00,927 --> 00:06:02,060
I wanted to clarify

86
00:06:02,061 --> 00:06:05,564
because it could be interpreted
as asking what she used to hit him.

87
00:06:05,565 --> 00:06:08,868
The context clearly points to the trigger.
Come on, translate.

88
00:06:15,408 --> 00:06:17,944
- "A slap in the face."
- What?

89
00:06:18,578 --> 00:06:19,979
You mean, your husband?

90
00:06:26,452 --> 00:06:28,688
"Aren't we talking about my husband?"

91
00:06:29,655 --> 00:06:32,525
Has that kind of thing happened before?

92
00:06:34,460 --> 00:06:36,094
What do you mean by "that kind of thing"?

93
00:06:36,095 --> 00:06:38,297
Now what? Come on, translate.

94
00:06:44,871 --> 00:06:46,305
All the time.

95
00:06:47,540 --> 00:06:51,377
I hit her first?
Is that what that woman is saying?

96
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:57,683
Look at my face.
Isn't it obvious I'm the victim here?

97
00:06:58,251 --> 00:07:00,419
It's a typical case.

98
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:03,522
The husband was routinely abusing
his wife physically.

99
00:07:03,523 --> 00:07:06,658
The wife had had it
and finally hit him back today.

100
00:07:06,659 --> 00:07:08,827
She did look like a strong-willed woman.

101
00:07:08,828 --> 00:07:10,095
True.

102
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:14,399
Talk to their neighbors
and the wife's friends, just in case.

103
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:17,402
She may have told them
about her husband's abuse.

104
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:18,638
Understood, sir.

105
00:07:29,649 --> 00:07:31,451
May I be excused then?

106
00:07:33,886 --> 00:07:34,821
Mr. Arikino?

107
00:07:38,858 --> 00:07:41,594
Now that you're no longer a cop,
how are things going?

108
00:07:44,330 --> 00:07:48,166
You may think you're better
now that you're an interpreter.

109
00:07:48,167 --> 00:07:50,068
But you are a former cop.

110
00:07:50,069 --> 00:07:51,570
I need you to understand the context

111
00:07:51,571 --> 00:07:54,073
of the questioning without asking me
each time.

112
00:08:03,749 --> 00:08:05,784
You must be exhausted, Ashan.

113
00:08:05,785 --> 00:08:07,353
Shall we take a break now?

114
00:08:35,348 --> 00:08:38,250
All right, everyone.
Let's question them all at once.

115
00:08:38,251 --> 00:08:39,851
Yes, sir.

116
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:41,153
Come this way.

117
00:08:43,155 --> 00:08:45,557
- Hey, Koda!
- Yes, Mr. Tarao.

118
00:08:45,558 --> 00:08:48,460
Send the interpreter you have now
over to us.

119
00:08:48,461 --> 00:08:49,961
Why is that?

120
00:08:49,962 --> 00:08:54,299
We raided a trading company
attempting to smuggle stolen car parts.

121
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,168
We'll find out where they get their parts.

122
00:08:58,437 --> 00:09:01,306
Even so, it's not fair to me.

123
00:09:01,307 --> 00:09:04,343
Your case involves
electric bike battery theft, doesn't it?

124
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:07,813
Our case is far more significant
than yours.

125
00:09:09,582 --> 00:09:11,017
But still...

126
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:13,085
Arikeeno.

127
00:09:13,853 --> 00:09:15,154
Come over here.

128
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:17,490
- Arikeeno?
- Just for a moment.

129
00:09:18,257 --> 00:09:19,724
What is it?

130
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:23,328
They're demanding
I give up Ms. Kiyomiya for them,

131
00:09:23,329 --> 00:09:25,865
but do you know anyone else
who can speak Sinhala?

132
00:09:27,266 --> 00:09:30,001
Among our full-time staff,
Kiyomiya is the only one.

133
00:09:30,002 --> 00:09:32,238
The others are part-time interpreters.

134
00:09:33,639 --> 00:09:36,142
So, tell me, Koda.

135
00:09:36,976 --> 00:09:39,979
You expect us to request
for part-time interpreters?

136
00:09:41,514 --> 00:09:43,848
I bet you're getting too involved
with the suspect.

137
00:09:43,849 --> 00:09:46,251
You're wasting time
discussing unrelated things

138
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,420
like their homeland and food, aren't you?

139
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:51,958
I just want to know the situation
that led him to commit the crime.

140
00:09:52,792 --> 00:09:55,260
You say they're unrelated.

141
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:59,097
But don't you think information
about his homeland and life is crucial

142
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:01,199
to understanding his background?

143
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,603
Don't you agree with me, Arikeeno?

144
00:10:05,004 --> 00:10:05,838
How about

145
00:10:06,906 --> 00:10:10,141
having Kiyomiya assist
with your questioning?

146
00:10:10,142 --> 00:10:13,346
If Miss Koda still needs an interpreter,
I'll ask my supervisor

147
00:10:13,913 --> 00:10:15,514
to send a part-time one.

148
00:10:16,248 --> 00:10:17,083
Arikeeno?

149
00:10:17,650 --> 00:10:18,951
Attaboy!

150
00:10:19,719 --> 00:10:21,387
I won't expect anything less

151
00:10:22,421 --> 00:10:23,756
from a former cop.

152
00:10:24,523 --> 00:10:25,391
Wait a minute.

153
00:10:43,709 --> 00:10:45,811
DAIKON, NAPA CABBAGE

154
00:11:09,535 --> 00:11:11,170
Arikeeno is such a traitor.

155
00:11:12,171 --> 00:11:13,372
Wait a minute.

156
00:11:23,315 --> 00:11:26,018
Mari? Mari?

157
00:11:27,119 --> 00:11:28,020
Mari!

158
00:11:29,422 --> 00:11:30,922
Are you all right?

159
00:11:30,923 --> 00:11:34,060
Yes. I'm all right.

160
00:11:41,934 --> 00:11:43,436
Um...

161
00:11:45,337 --> 00:11:47,006
Tell me,

162
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:50,309
are you in a relationship with anyone now?

163
00:11:51,143 --> 00:11:52,278
Huh?

164
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:54,679
Of course, not.

165
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:57,315
I have a job like this,

166
00:11:57,316 --> 00:11:58,918
and I just don't meet anyone.

167
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:02,221
Police officers are encouraged

168
00:12:02,988 --> 00:12:05,357
to find partners
through workplace romance.

169
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:08,027
Workplace romance?

170
00:12:08,594 --> 00:12:10,296
Well, basically, it means

171
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,733
you work at the same place.

172
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:15,534
Then you get married.

173
00:12:17,937 --> 00:12:21,807
If your partner is also a police officer,
there's no need for a background check.

174
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:24,209
They often say things like,

175
00:12:24,210 --> 00:12:27,479
"Are you and so-and-so dating?"

176
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:31,150
I find it really annoying.

177
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:33,285
Mari,

178
00:12:33,853 --> 00:12:35,588
you'll be in high demand in China.

179
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:37,523
- You think?
- Definitely.

180
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:41,960
China has a large number of men

181
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:43,796
and very few women.

182
00:12:44,530 --> 00:12:49,502
So, men in China
have a hard time finding someone to marry.

183
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:54,106
You don't stand a chance
without enough height and money.

184
00:12:55,107 --> 00:12:56,108
That's interesting.

185
00:12:58,077 --> 00:13:00,845
Before I came to Japan,

186
00:13:00,846 --> 00:13:04,682
my childhood friend confessed his love
to me near my house.

187
00:13:04,683 --> 00:13:05,718
Really?

188
00:13:07,419 --> 00:13:08,821
What is he like?

189
00:13:09,522 --> 00:13:12,290
Although we were childhood friends,

190
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:14,894
we hadn't seen each other in a long time.

191
00:13:15,694 --> 00:13:16,561
Out of the blue,

192
00:13:16,562 --> 00:13:19,498
he told me he'd been hired
by a great company.

193
00:13:20,199 --> 00:13:21,699
And then he asked me,

194
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:25,304
"Don't you think I'd be a good candidate
as your marriage partner?"

195
00:13:26,539 --> 00:13:28,306
How do I say this in Japanese?

196
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:29,875
Um...

197
00:13:30,376 --> 00:13:32,210
It feels a little funny to me.

198
00:13:32,211 --> 00:13:34,713
As if he was just making an easy decision.

199
00:13:36,549 --> 00:13:37,550
Right?

200
00:13:38,784 --> 00:13:41,020
Yes, that's it.

201
00:13:41,620 --> 00:13:43,521
You think?

202
00:13:43,522 --> 00:13:44,923
What the heck is that?

203
00:13:44,924 --> 00:13:47,293
You don't think it was?

204
00:13:49,228 --> 00:13:52,697
But I can't deny that his approach

205
00:13:52,698 --> 00:13:54,867
wasn't exactly romantic.

206
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:02,842
Is that interpreter married?

207
00:14:04,009 --> 00:14:06,745
Interpreter? You mean Arikeeno?

208
00:14:08,781 --> 00:14:10,749
I have no idea.

209
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:13,052
I've never asked him about it.

210
00:14:19,158 --> 00:14:20,492
Do you want to know?

211
00:14:23,262 --> 00:14:25,865
Yes. Very much.

212
00:14:28,968 --> 00:14:29,834
Shen,

213
00:14:29,835 --> 00:14:31,103
you are so adorable.

214
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:37,742
WHY DID YOU HIT YOUR HUSBAND?
A SLAP IN THE FACE.

215
00:14:37,743 --> 00:14:39,245
<i>Why did you hit your husband?</i>

216
00:14:40,846 --> 00:14:41,713
A slap in the face.

217
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:43,481
You mean, your husband?

218
00:14:43,482 --> 00:14:45,084
Aren't we talking about my husband?

219
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:48,287
Has that kind of thing happened before?

220
00:14:49,321 --> 00:14:50,623
All the time.

221
00:14:57,830 --> 00:15:01,100
MARI KODA

222
00:15:16,982 --> 00:15:18,216
Hello?

223
00:15:18,217 --> 00:15:22,353
- Good.
- It's good.

224
00:15:22,354 --> 00:15:23,288
Eat.

225
00:15:23,289 --> 00:15:24,456
- It's good to eat.
- It's good to eat.

226
00:15:27,192 --> 00:15:29,662
Look, he's here. Arikeeno, over here.

227
00:15:31,163 --> 00:15:32,563
See, he came.

228
00:15:32,564 --> 00:15:36,000
He usually accepts my invitations.

229
00:15:36,001 --> 00:15:37,435
Are you pretty drunk?

230
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:41,040
Not at all. Is beer okay with you?
This one's on me.

231
00:15:46,578 --> 00:15:49,547
It's nice to see you. You look well.

232
00:15:49,548 --> 00:15:50,916
Nice to see you, too.

233
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:52,751
Shen,

234
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:55,453
your Japanese has improved so much.

235
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:58,056
Yes, thanks to Mari.

236
00:15:58,057 --> 00:16:01,727
I sometimes meet Mari
and learn Japanese from her.

237
00:16:02,494 --> 00:16:03,661
Oh, you do?

238
00:16:03,662 --> 00:16:06,164
Come on, you two. Lift your beers.

239
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:08,100
Cheers!

240
00:16:19,545 --> 00:16:21,880
What was it
you wanted to talk to me about?

241
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:25,584
Shen has something to ask you.

242
00:16:27,052 --> 00:16:28,087
You do?

243
00:16:29,822 --> 00:16:31,590
Shen. Go ahead. Ask him.

244
00:16:34,026 --> 00:16:37,930
Um... Well...

245
00:16:42,735 --> 00:16:47,106
What is it like to work as an interpreter?

246
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:49,641
Work as an interpreter?

247
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:53,778
Shen says she wants to help people

248
00:16:53,779 --> 00:16:56,582
communicate with each other,
just like you do.

249
00:16:58,183 --> 00:17:01,285
It would be great if you two
could work together someday.

250
00:17:01,286 --> 00:17:02,588
And more, you know?

251
00:17:04,723 --> 00:17:06,558
Work as an interpreter...

252
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:09,695
There are roughly three types
of interpreting.

253
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,597
The first is simultaneous interpreting.

254
00:17:12,598 --> 00:17:15,400
Oh, I know! I see that a lot on TV.
That's what they use

255
00:17:15,401 --> 00:17:18,336
for speeches on live broadcasts, right?

256
00:17:18,337 --> 00:17:21,707
That's right. You interpret the speaker
in real time as they speak.

257
00:17:22,508 --> 00:17:25,610
The second type is known as whispering.

258
00:17:25,611 --> 00:17:27,111
Wait, can I interrupt for a second?

259
00:17:27,112 --> 00:17:28,646
What is it?

260
00:17:28,647 --> 00:17:30,181
I'm talking to Shen right now.

261
00:17:30,182 --> 00:17:31,149
I'm so sorry.

262
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:34,853
I'm going to grab some more drinks
at the bar. Can I get you anything?

263
00:17:36,155 --> 00:17:37,222
I'm good.

264
00:17:38,323 --> 00:17:40,592
All right, maybe I'll order some food
as well.

265
00:17:45,697 --> 00:17:47,900
"Maybe I'll order some food as well."

266
00:17:50,169 --> 00:17:51,336
Thank you so much.

267
00:17:52,638 --> 00:17:55,406
Whispering directly
into the listener's ear like that

268
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:56,775
is called whispering.

269
00:17:58,544 --> 00:18:01,679
Its method is similar
to simultaneous interpreting,

270
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,349
but it's more common
since it doesn't need heavy equipment.

271
00:18:05,350 --> 00:18:07,018
But in our field,

272
00:18:07,019 --> 00:18:10,021
we don't do simultaneous interpreting
or whispering.

273
00:18:10,022 --> 00:18:11,823
We rely on consecutive interpreting.

274
00:18:11,824 --> 00:18:12,757
CONSECUTIVE INTERPRETING

275
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:14,959
Consecutive interpreting? And that's...

276
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,795
There.

277
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:19,497
What in the world did you order?

278
00:18:19,498 --> 00:18:21,567
Let's see...

279
00:18:22,134 --> 00:18:25,036
I picked up some olives
and fish and chips.

280
00:18:25,037 --> 00:18:27,339
And... I don't remember what this was.

281
00:18:30,242 --> 00:18:31,543
"Let's see...

282
00:18:32,211 --> 00:18:34,679
I picked up some olives
and fish and chips.

283
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,381
And... I don't remember what this was."

284
00:18:37,316 --> 00:18:39,584
So that was...

285
00:18:39,585 --> 00:18:40,519
That's right.

286
00:18:41,086 --> 00:18:42,421
Could you tell the difference?

287
00:18:43,489 --> 00:18:46,592
- You interpreted all of it, didn't you?
- Yes, I did.

288
00:18:47,159 --> 00:18:51,997
You interpret every word the speaker says,
including mistakes and fillers.

289
00:18:52,564 --> 00:18:54,199
This is consecutive interpreting.

290
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:56,268
That's interesting.

291
00:18:57,169 --> 00:18:58,303
It's like impersonation.

292
00:19:00,739 --> 00:19:04,842
In consecutive interpreting,
accuracy is more important than speed.

293
00:19:04,843 --> 00:19:07,245
You can't change the sentence order.

294
00:19:07,246 --> 00:19:09,348
If you do, the meaning could change.

295
00:19:10,015 --> 00:19:11,849
You also need to interpret

296
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:14,686
the emotions and nuances
as faithfully as possible.

297
00:19:16,522 --> 00:19:18,723
Even still,

298
00:19:18,724 --> 00:19:22,427
the need for consecutive interpreting
is often underestimated.

299
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:28,233
It could affect the lives
of suspects or victims,

300
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:32,371
and sometimes could cost a life.

301
00:19:35,274 --> 00:19:37,141
Arikeeno,

302
00:19:37,142 --> 00:19:40,846
you assist so many cases in a day.

303
00:19:41,713 --> 00:19:44,116
And you've seen all types
of police officers.

304
00:19:48,754 --> 00:19:51,023
Do you want the same things?
I'll go order them.

305
00:19:58,764 --> 00:20:01,866
I had way too much to drink.

306
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:04,569
Mari, are you all right?

307
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:06,704
I'm completely all right.

308
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:08,239
By the way,

309
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:11,042
what were you talking about
with Arikeeno earlier?

310
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:13,311
All kinds of things

311
00:20:13,312 --> 00:20:16,481
like interpreting for the police force
and...

312
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:22,754
We also talked about how Shen
was suddenly proposed to on the street.

313
00:20:23,455 --> 00:20:26,023
What was that?

314
00:20:26,024 --> 00:20:28,593
She had this friend
she hadn't seen in years.

315
00:20:28,594 --> 00:20:33,198
He had been in love with her all this time
and unexpectedly confessed his love.

316
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,335
Is that the way the story went?

317
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:39,070
I thought he had struggled
to find a partner...

318
00:20:39,071 --> 00:20:41,306
- Mari!
- ...and saw her as an easy choice for him.

319
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,044
What was that?

320
00:20:47,179 --> 00:20:48,780
What did you just say?

321
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:53,552
Did you say, "slap in your face"?

322
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:58,991
No, no, no. That's not it.

323
00:20:59,725 --> 00:21:03,127
It's something like a teen slang

324
00:21:03,128 --> 00:21:06,598
or a trendy phrase that young people use.

325
00:21:12,004 --> 00:21:16,507
It could also mean
something like "a lie was exposed."

326
00:21:16,508 --> 00:21:18,043
"A lie was exposed..."

327
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:21,380
Why did you hit your husband?

328
00:21:22,214 --> 00:21:24,148
His lie was exposed.

329
00:21:24,149 --> 00:21:27,218
I wanted to make it sound a little nicer.

330
00:21:27,219 --> 00:21:28,353
Shen,

331
00:21:29,554 --> 00:21:31,923
thank you. You are wonderful.

332
00:21:33,692 --> 00:21:35,260
I'm leaving now.

333
00:21:35,861 --> 00:21:38,430
What? Arikeeno?

334
00:21:40,565 --> 00:21:41,533
What's wrong with him?

335
00:21:44,603 --> 00:21:48,307
The husband, who was the victim,
had been having multiple affairs.

336
00:21:48,940 --> 00:21:51,342
On the day of the incident,
he lied to his wife,

337
00:21:51,343 --> 00:21:54,379
saying he was off to work,
but he was meeting another woman.

338
00:21:55,013 --> 00:21:58,750
She found out, and it led to a fight
between them.

339
00:21:59,551 --> 00:22:00,719
I see.

340
00:22:01,620 --> 00:22:02,621
Does that mean

341
00:22:03,422 --> 00:22:07,626
our brilliant interpreter
misunderstood the statement?

342
00:22:09,561 --> 00:22:10,762
I apologize.

343
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:15,767
To sum it up,

344
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:18,169
it was our interpreter's fault.

345
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:21,039
The interpreter here
misunderstood your statement.

346
00:22:21,573 --> 00:22:23,875
While you were speaking rhetorically,

347
00:22:24,476 --> 00:22:26,445
he took your words literally.

348
00:22:27,646 --> 00:22:28,880
We apologize.

349
00:22:31,717 --> 00:22:33,884
"To sum it up,
it was our interpreter's fault.

350
00:22:33,885 --> 00:22:37,022
While you were speaking rhetorically,

351
00:22:37,622 --> 00:22:41,560
he took your words literally.
We apologize."

352
00:22:43,328 --> 00:22:47,632
Mistakes like this
in interpreting shouldn't happen at all.

353
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:52,303
As a police force, we consider it
an urgent matter

354
00:22:52,304 --> 00:22:55,005
to improve our interpreters' skills.

355
00:22:55,006 --> 00:22:58,410
We are deeply sorry for our failure.

356
00:23:00,879 --> 00:23:06,917
"Mistakes like this in interpreting
shouldn't happen at all.

357
00:23:06,918 --> 00:23:10,287
As a police force, we consider it
an urgent matter

358
00:23:10,288 --> 00:23:12,456
to improve our interpreters' skills.

359
00:23:12,457 --> 00:23:16,094
We are deeply sorry for our failure."

360
00:23:17,763 --> 00:23:20,132
Is that it? Come on.

361
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,501
Stand up.

362
00:23:27,472 --> 00:23:30,142
I'm truly sorry
I misinterpreted your words.

363
00:23:40,051 --> 00:23:41,453
Tell me, sir.

364
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:46,158
You were just interpreting exactly
what the detective said, right?

365
00:23:46,725 --> 00:23:47,926
That's correct.

366
00:23:48,693 --> 00:23:49,627
That means

367
00:23:49,628 --> 00:23:52,864
this man is making you repeat
his nasty remarks about you.

368
00:23:54,032 --> 00:23:56,234
What a jerk he is!

369
00:23:57,502 --> 00:24:01,406
Even if I don't know the language,
I can tell just by his face.

370
00:24:02,774 --> 00:24:05,844
His attitude shows
that he's looking down on me.

371
00:24:08,647 --> 00:24:12,484
You said you made a mistake,
but I had my faults, too.

372
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:15,553
Out of frustration,

373
00:24:15,554 --> 00:24:18,023
I intentionally used
a confusing expression.

374
00:24:20,358 --> 00:24:21,759
What is she saying?

375
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:24,062
You were such a gentleman.

376
00:24:25,430 --> 00:24:28,733
I could see your sincere heart.

377
00:24:32,771 --> 00:24:33,972
Translate!

378
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:36,775
What are you laughing about?

379
00:24:37,442 --> 00:24:38,609
PAULA RESTAURANT AND BAR

380
00:24:38,610 --> 00:24:40,377
Here you go.

381
00:24:40,378 --> 00:24:42,948
This is the Banana Leaf Curry.

382
00:24:53,658 --> 00:24:55,160
It's so good!

383
00:24:55,727 --> 00:24:56,895
Here is the Fish Roll.

384
00:25:03,668 --> 00:25:04,669
And the pudding.

385
00:25:15,914 --> 00:25:19,751
I came here today to ask you about Ashan.

386
00:25:22,287 --> 00:25:23,855
Our Ashan

387
00:25:25,223 --> 00:25:26,724
was such a hardworking guy.

388
00:25:26,725 --> 00:25:27,992
ASHAN - I'LL DO MY BEST!!

389
00:25:27,993 --> 00:25:30,961
You know the Sri Lankan economy
collapsed, don't you?

390
00:25:30,962 --> 00:25:33,864
He was so worried about his family

391
00:25:33,865 --> 00:25:35,800
that he wanted to bring them here.

392
00:25:38,436 --> 00:25:39,570
The truth is,

393
00:25:39,571 --> 00:25:43,608
many of our guys
are in similar circumstances.

394
00:25:45,510 --> 00:25:48,747
Even so, I can't believe
he would resort to stealing.

395
00:25:52,350 --> 00:25:55,720
You know what I thought about Ashan?

396
00:25:56,855 --> 00:25:59,823
He claims he stole
on the spur of the moment.

397
00:25:59,824 --> 00:26:02,226
But stealing electric bike batteries

398
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:04,729
feels a bit too much
like a professional job.

399
00:26:06,031 --> 00:26:07,565
So, let me ask you this.

400
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:09,967
Is there anyone suspicious

401
00:26:09,968 --> 00:26:11,736
in his circle of friends?

402
00:26:14,005 --> 00:26:15,040
Anyone suspicious?

403
00:26:32,757 --> 00:26:33,658
Excuse me.

404
00:26:34,392 --> 00:26:35,727
You're Ranga, right?

405
00:26:37,028 --> 00:26:39,064
Can I talk to you for a second?

406
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:42,000
I didn't do it.

407
00:26:42,834 --> 00:26:44,368
I'm telling you the truth. I didn't do it.

408
00:26:44,369 --> 00:26:46,470
Calm down.

409
00:26:46,471 --> 00:26:47,872
It's all right.

410
00:26:48,473 --> 00:26:50,275
I will believe you,

411
00:26:51,910 --> 00:26:54,446
so can you tell me what happened?

412
00:26:56,881 --> 00:26:59,317
There was a time
when I desperately needed money.

413
00:26:59,985 --> 00:27:03,421
Someone I met told me
that if I had bicycle batteries,

414
00:27:04,889 --> 00:27:06,291
he would buy them from me.

415
00:27:08,293 --> 00:27:12,163
I merely passed that information along
to Ashan.

416
00:27:15,033 --> 00:27:15,934
Listen.

417
00:27:16,835 --> 00:27:21,139
Can you tell me more about that man?

418
00:27:23,875 --> 00:27:25,710
You do know this man, don't you?

419
00:27:27,712 --> 00:27:32,550
His name is Ando Ryugo, a former gangster.
And now, leader of a car theft gang.

420
00:27:39,224 --> 00:27:42,594
We do know that Ando
regularly visited your office.

421
00:27:51,403 --> 00:27:55,440
<i>You bought stolen car parts from Ando and
tried to smuggle them abroad, didn't you?</i>

422
00:28:08,186 --> 00:28:11,221
This guy just won't talk,

423
00:28:11,222 --> 00:28:13,591
and we can't figure out where Ando is.

424
00:28:22,233 --> 00:28:24,703
The trade company we raided
is run by Nigerians.

425
00:28:25,403 --> 00:28:28,138
The documents we confiscated
are in various languages,

426
00:28:28,139 --> 00:28:31,442
including Chinese, Sinhala, Russian,
and Portuguese, all mixed up.

427
00:28:31,443 --> 00:28:34,446
- Will you please go through them?
- Yes, sir.

428
00:28:41,286 --> 00:28:43,788
We know you purchased the parts from Ando.

429
00:28:46,891 --> 00:28:48,626
How long are you going to play dumb?

430
00:28:49,394 --> 00:28:51,863
<i>Uthman, the Nigerian man,
appears to know no Japanese.</i>

431
00:28:52,497 --> 00:28:55,400
<i>He is quite tricky,
making the questioning challenging.</i>

432
00:28:56,601 --> 00:29:00,404
Ando probably knows
that a raid took place.

433
00:29:00,405 --> 00:29:03,173
We need to move fast, or he will flee.

434
00:29:03,174 --> 00:29:05,709
If Uthman doesn't talk at all,

435
00:29:05,710 --> 00:29:08,045
get information about Ando
from the others.

436
00:29:08,046 --> 00:29:09,180
Yes, sir.

437
00:29:10,381 --> 00:29:13,550
Excuse me, I'm not sure if it's Ando, but...

438
00:29:13,551 --> 00:29:14,785
What is it?

439
00:29:14,786 --> 00:29:17,588
You know Ashan, the Sri Lankan suspect?

440
00:29:17,589 --> 00:29:21,558
He claims that he was instructed
by a former Japanese gangster

441
00:29:21,559 --> 00:29:25,029
to steal batteries from electric bicycles.

442
00:29:25,697 --> 00:29:29,200
You had three batteries in your backpack.

443
00:29:29,934 --> 00:29:31,870
What were you going to do with them?

444
00:29:32,470 --> 00:29:33,805
Were you selling them to someone?

445
00:29:34,372 --> 00:29:36,007
Electric bicycle batteries?

446
00:29:37,442 --> 00:29:39,210
Isn't that the case Koda is working on?

447
00:29:40,245 --> 00:29:41,279
Yes, it is.

448
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:43,915
Shakuno, where the heck is Koda?

449
00:29:45,216 --> 00:29:48,185
Is she out doing legwork on her own again

450
00:29:48,186 --> 00:29:51,088
when even the First Division
might get involved with the case?

451
00:29:51,089 --> 00:29:54,592
UTHMAN OKONKWO

452
00:29:57,495 --> 00:29:58,729
Good afternoon.

453
00:29:58,730 --> 00:30:00,230
Excuse me.

454
00:30:00,231 --> 00:30:02,734
Do you notice anything odd
about the Nigerian man

455
00:30:03,434 --> 00:30:04,869
you're interpreting for?

456
00:30:07,405 --> 00:30:09,674
Well, he's definitely odd.

457
00:30:10,842 --> 00:30:11,910
<i>As a matter of fact,</i>

458
00:30:12,710 --> 00:30:15,413
I think he understands everything
when we speak Japanese.

459
00:30:17,215 --> 00:30:19,817
<i>When he heard
that Ando's whereabouts were unknown,</i>

460
00:30:19,818 --> 00:30:21,486
<i>it seemed like he smirked.</i>

461
00:30:21,986 --> 00:30:24,823
It's possible that he's married
to a Japanese woman.

462
00:30:26,090 --> 00:30:28,058
I told that to the detective just now.

463
00:30:28,059 --> 00:30:29,194
That's what I thought.

464
00:30:29,928 --> 00:30:30,895
Excuse me?

465
00:30:38,369 --> 00:30:39,871
Hello, is anyone here?

466
00:30:43,942 --> 00:30:47,011
I'm with the Higashi Shinjuku
Police Station.

467
00:30:48,613 --> 00:30:51,616
Do you know someone
by the name of Ashan Kakuchi?

468
00:30:53,952 --> 00:30:54,953
I guess no one's here.

469
00:31:02,093 --> 00:31:03,995
Hello, Mr. Shack? What's the matter?

470
00:31:04,562 --> 00:31:05,864
Koda, where are you now?

471
00:31:06,431 --> 00:31:08,433
I'm doing some legwork in Shinjuku.

472
00:31:09,601 --> 00:31:12,970
Please don't tell the boss
that I'm on my own.

473
00:31:12,971 --> 00:31:14,105
<i>I'm right here.</i>

474
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:18,442
The electric bicycle battery theft case
you're investigating

475
00:31:18,443 --> 00:31:21,511
might be linked
to our stolen car parts case.

476
00:31:21,512 --> 00:31:24,148
<i>Come back to the police station
and report what you know.</i>

477
00:31:24,716 --> 00:31:27,952
The person we're looking for
goes by the name Ryugo Ando.

478
00:31:28,820 --> 00:31:30,088
<i>Ryugo Ando?</i>

479
00:31:31,489 --> 00:31:33,358
<i>I think I just...</i>

480
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:36,094
<i>Let go...</i>

481
00:31:37,295 --> 00:31:38,695
- Koda?
- <i>Mr. Ando.</i>

482
00:31:38,696 --> 00:31:41,132
What's going on? Koda?

483
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,067
The phone's been switched off.

484
00:31:44,068 --> 00:31:47,104
She shouldn't have gone by herself.

485
00:31:47,105 --> 00:31:50,475
Mr. Shakuno, which room
is Uthman being questioned in?

486
00:31:51,676 --> 00:31:55,445
- Tell me quickly!
- Mr. Ando, please calm down. Hold on.

487
00:31:55,446 --> 00:31:56,680
Shut up!

488
00:31:56,681 --> 00:31:58,949
I'm here just to ask a few questions.

489
00:31:58,950 --> 00:32:01,518
Darn it! You're a cop, seriously?

490
00:32:01,519 --> 00:32:02,854
Hold on.

491
00:32:07,058 --> 00:32:10,828
Were you heading somewhere on a trip?

492
00:32:13,598 --> 00:32:15,099
You think I'm an idiot or what?

493
00:32:16,167 --> 00:32:18,136
The other officers will arrive shortly.

494
00:32:18,870 --> 00:32:20,204
Don't do anything reckless.

495
00:32:48,566 --> 00:32:49,667
Koda.

496
00:33:07,885 --> 00:33:09,087
- Get the knife, please.
- Yes!

497
00:33:11,055 --> 00:33:12,657
I'm handcuffing him.

498
00:33:17,228 --> 00:33:19,397
I got him. He's under control now.

499
00:33:22,033 --> 00:33:23,568
Miss Koda, are you all right?

500
00:33:31,209 --> 00:33:33,443
A patrol car is coming through.

501
00:33:33,444 --> 00:33:35,613
POLICE

502
00:33:43,554 --> 00:33:45,923
What in the world were you thinking?

503
00:33:48,092 --> 00:33:49,227
I'm so sorry.

504
00:33:53,197 --> 00:33:54,198
But...

505
00:33:55,033 --> 00:33:56,434
how did you know I was here?

506
00:33:58,703 --> 00:34:02,407
Mr. Arikino walked into the room
where Uthman was being questioned.

507
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:05,042
Where is Ando's office?

508
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:06,743
How dare you burst in like this?

509
00:34:06,744 --> 00:34:08,112
Tell me now.

510
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:11,783
You understand Japanese, don't you?

511
00:34:12,750 --> 00:34:16,387
I know you've been writing emails
and contracts in Japanese.

512
00:34:17,155 --> 00:34:19,424
I know you're fluent in Japanese.

513
00:34:24,996 --> 00:34:27,498
He is an interpreter.

514
00:34:28,232 --> 00:34:29,834
He went way beyond his role.

515
00:34:31,102 --> 00:34:34,806
We got Ando, and you're safe,
but he shouldn't get away with this.

516
00:34:36,407 --> 00:34:39,043
You need to acknowledge
that your actions were wrong.

517
00:34:45,249 --> 00:34:48,853
So, he made the first move
with the knife, correct?

518
00:34:49,887 --> 00:34:51,122
That's correct.

519
00:35:02,366 --> 00:35:04,001
Why did you go there alone?

520
00:35:10,007 --> 00:35:11,275
As for Ashan,

521
00:35:12,276 --> 00:35:13,811
he did steal bicycle batteries.

522
00:35:15,346 --> 00:35:17,582
He needs to face punishment
for what he did.

523
00:35:19,016 --> 00:35:20,151
But I wondered

524
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:25,223
if someone had led him down
the wrong path in life.

525
00:35:26,257 --> 00:35:29,060
If so, I felt we should also go
after that person.

526
00:35:35,433 --> 00:35:36,968
I don't mean to make an excuse.

527
00:35:38,669 --> 00:35:40,805
But if I had known
Ando was a former gangster,

528
00:35:41,706 --> 00:35:43,207
I wouldn't have gone there alone.

529
00:35:48,212 --> 00:35:49,247
I'm sorry

530
00:35:52,250 --> 00:35:54,085
I made you do something unnecessary.

531
00:35:55,786 --> 00:35:57,555
I risked your safety as well.

532
00:35:59,891 --> 00:36:01,325
You must be upset with me.

533
00:36:02,260 --> 00:36:03,361
Are you, Arikeeno?

534
00:36:04,762 --> 00:36:06,264
It's not that I'm upset.

535
00:36:08,633 --> 00:36:09,700
You might fall someday

536
00:36:12,637 --> 00:36:15,439
if you follow only your convictions
in this organization.

537
00:36:16,741 --> 00:36:18,109
You'll reach a point of no return.

538
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:35,492
We've been encountering
more cases in Higashi Shinjuku

539
00:36:35,493 --> 00:36:38,995
involving gang groups and foreigners
conspiring to commit crimes.

540
00:36:38,996 --> 00:36:43,066
But we are guided by the motto
that "adversity makes a man wise."

541
00:36:43,067 --> 00:36:44,501
I didn't get what you said.

542
00:36:44,502 --> 00:36:46,102
I meant that many hardships will--

543
00:36:46,103 --> 00:36:47,637
- I was not asking.
- Oh.

544
00:36:47,638 --> 00:36:51,107
We found traces of Uthman's
business activities throughout Tokyo.

545
00:36:51,108 --> 00:36:52,042
RYUTA YANAGI
(TOKYO METROPOLITAN POLICE FIRST DIVISION)

546
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:53,911
Please disclose the questioning details.

547
00:36:55,379 --> 00:36:56,581
Understood, sir.

548
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:00,151
By the way,

549
00:37:00,718 --> 00:37:03,920
I heard it was a close call
for your sergeant.

550
00:37:03,921 --> 00:37:07,123
Fortunately,
she only sustained a minor injury.

551
00:37:07,124 --> 00:37:11,394
If she hadn't been investigating
the bicycle battery theft case,

552
00:37:11,395 --> 00:37:13,063
we wouldn't have found Ando.

553
00:37:13,064 --> 00:37:16,099
And it's frightening to think about
what might have happened

554
00:37:16,100 --> 00:37:17,635
without Mr. Arikino's quick action.

555
00:37:18,336 --> 00:37:19,302
Arikino?

556
00:37:19,303 --> 00:37:22,073
He's the interpreter
that Koda is close to.

557
00:37:30,815 --> 00:37:33,351
STATEMENT OF RESPONSIBILITY

558
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:40,691
I'm starving.

559
00:37:44,362 --> 00:37:45,963
Miss Koda?

560
00:37:46,931 --> 00:37:49,633
Ta-dah! Here are some <i>xianbing</i>.

561
00:37:49,634 --> 00:37:50,700
They're for you.

562
00:37:50,701 --> 00:37:53,271
You brought me Chinese meat pies?

563
00:37:54,372 --> 00:37:56,207
I'm heading home now.

564
00:37:56,707 --> 00:37:58,608
Don't overwork yourself.

565
00:37:58,609 --> 00:37:59,843
Thank you.

566
00:37:59,844 --> 00:38:01,312
- See you tomorrow.
- Thank you.

567
00:38:04,548 --> 00:38:06,217
It looks so good.

568
00:38:14,392 --> 00:38:15,459
It's so delicious.

569
00:38:19,864 --> 00:38:20,865
Excuse me.

570
00:38:21,599 --> 00:38:24,602
- May I speak to you for a moment?
- Good evening, sir.

571
00:38:25,569 --> 00:38:27,037
Are you from the First Division?

572
00:38:27,038 --> 00:38:28,773
What's your relationship with Arikino?

573
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:33,044
- Do you know him?
- Just answer my question.

574
00:38:35,112 --> 00:38:37,180
Well, how can I say it?

575
00:38:37,181 --> 00:38:41,418
We spent the whole night together.

576
00:38:41,419 --> 00:38:43,119
Of course, for the investigation.

577
00:38:43,120 --> 00:38:46,524
And we sometimes go out to eat together.

578
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:49,293
You seem close to him,

579
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:52,396
but do you even have a clue about him?

580
00:38:54,398 --> 00:38:55,333
Excuse me?

581
00:39:11,482 --> 00:39:12,550
Look who's here.

582
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:17,788
You were still open?

583
00:39:20,324 --> 00:39:21,958
What happened

584
00:39:21,959 --> 00:39:25,629
to that girl with the green hair
you were with last time?

585
00:39:27,198 --> 00:39:28,933
I'm sorry about what I did last time.

586
00:39:33,938 --> 00:39:35,239
You came here to drink?

587
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:37,942
I guess it's been three years.

588
00:39:40,010 --> 00:39:41,812
What the heck is going on?

589
00:39:45,216 --> 00:39:48,953
When I used to see you a lot,
I learned all kinds of slang from you,

590
00:39:49,620 --> 00:39:51,422
but I have been lazy lately.

591
00:40:01,799 --> 00:40:03,100
There's only a little left,

592
00:40:03,701 --> 00:40:05,736
and there's no point in keeping it.

593
00:40:06,537 --> 00:40:09,206
If you finish it,
that would be a huge help for me.

594
00:40:11,542 --> 00:40:15,045
I'm sure that will make him happy, too.

595
00:40:22,686 --> 00:40:24,021
Brrr! It's so cold out.

596
00:40:26,023 --> 00:40:28,591
- Hey, there.
- Siwoo...

597
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:30,861
You've been banned
since the day before yesterday.

598
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:35,365
You disrupt the moral order of our bar.

599
00:40:35,366 --> 00:40:37,635
Why bother
when you don't have enough customers?

600
00:40:43,407 --> 00:40:44,542
Come on in, please.

601
00:40:46,677 --> 00:40:48,512
What did you want to talk about?

602
00:40:49,880 --> 00:40:52,715
Do you remember you told me before

603
00:40:52,716 --> 00:40:54,618
that Arikeeno used to be a cop?

604
00:40:55,286 --> 00:40:58,222
Do you know anything else about him?

605
00:40:59,223 --> 00:41:00,524
Anything else?

606
00:41:02,793 --> 00:41:05,996
What I know is all hearsay,
not first-hand information.

607
00:41:07,798 --> 00:41:09,467
Whatever it is, can you tell me?

608
00:41:13,204 --> 00:41:15,306
Keep in mind that it's just a rumor.

609
00:41:17,341 --> 00:41:21,544
The station worked hard to contain it,
preventing it from spreading.

610
00:41:21,545 --> 00:41:24,080
About three years ago,
a scandal article came out

611
00:41:24,081 --> 00:41:26,050
about the Kamiazabu Police Station.

612
00:41:26,650 --> 00:41:29,320
Kamiazabu is where
Arikeeno used to work, right?

613
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:31,255
Right.

614
00:41:32,089 --> 00:41:35,458
There's a rumor that Arikino was the one

615
00:41:35,459 --> 00:41:37,595
who leaked internal information
to a reporter.

616
00:41:38,896 --> 00:41:40,965
Arikeeno was the one
who leaked information?

617
00:41:42,766 --> 00:41:46,904
Not only that,
but the article led to someone's death.

618
00:42:03,621 --> 00:42:04,788
What do you do?

619
00:42:08,259 --> 00:42:09,493
Why don't you take a guess?

620
00:42:12,863 --> 00:42:13,931
You're a businessman.

621
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:15,666
You're out on the field?

622
00:42:17,868 --> 00:42:19,436
But you don't look like a sales person.

623
00:42:20,738 --> 00:42:22,506
You seem like a loner.

624
00:42:25,809 --> 00:42:28,145
Oh, I get it. You do IT maintenance
and management.

625
00:42:30,414 --> 00:42:32,715
That's right.

626
00:42:32,716 --> 00:42:34,118
You're definitely lying.

627
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:37,755
Your guess is not too far off.

628
00:42:43,227 --> 00:42:44,228
Then, this time,

629
00:42:45,296 --> 00:42:46,931
guess what kind of person I am.

630
00:42:57,541 --> 00:43:00,177
Why don't we get out of here
and go somewhere else?

631
00:43:06,684 --> 00:43:07,985
Maybe another time.

632
00:43:14,725 --> 00:43:15,758
KAMIAZABU POLICE STATION SCANDAL

633
00:43:15,759 --> 00:43:19,997
EXCLUSIVE SCOOP:
THE DARKNESS INSIDE THE POLICE FORCE!

634
00:43:22,366 --> 00:43:27,304
"DELIBERATE MISINTERPRETATION"
DURING QUESTIONING

635
00:43:33,877 --> 00:43:37,914
"DELIBERATE MISINTERPRETATION"

636
00:43:37,915 --> 00:43:41,250
A PERSON CLAIMING TO BE AN INSIDER
OF KAMIAZABU POLICE STATION...

637
00:43:41,251 --> 00:43:44,888
DATA WAS PROVIDED BY AN ANONYMOUS SOURCE

638
00:44:05,075 --> 00:44:07,577
Are you saying that Shun was kidnapped
because of me?

639
00:44:07,578 --> 00:44:08,778
Kidnapped?

640
00:44:08,779 --> 00:44:11,280
<i>I wonder if the kidnapping
and the citizenship trade</i>

641
00:44:11,281 --> 00:44:12,949
<i>are completely unrelated.</i>

642
00:44:12,950 --> 00:44:15,652
- You're doing your work perfectly.
- Right?

643
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:18,488
The baby's backside is about this size.

644
00:44:18,489 --> 00:44:21,859
<i>Banh mi</i> and Vietnamese coffee?
Coffee with condensed milk, right?

645
00:44:22,426 --> 00:44:24,528
<i>I'm asking you why on earth you are here.</i>
